# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .env.example — copy to `.env` for local overrides:  cp .env.example .env
#
# Precedence (highest first):
#   1. real OS environment variables (what Docker / CI inject)
#   2. .env               (your local, git-ignored overrides)
#   3. config/environments/<ENVIRONMENT>.env   (committed, non-secret defaults)
#
# NEVER put real secrets in committed files. Secrets are injected via the OS
# environment (Docker Compose `environment:` / CI secrets) — see docs/coding-standards.md.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Selects which profile file is loaded from config/environments/. One of: dev | test | prod
ENVIRONMENT=dev
# --- Service / API ---
SERVICE_NAME=api
API_HOST=0.0.0.0
API_PORT=8000
DEBUG=false
# --- Logging ---
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_FORMAT=json          # json | console
# --- Datastore connection strings ---
# Pooled at startup and probed by /ready (ADR 0005). Values below are safe local
# dev placeholders, NOT production secrets.
#
# Leave a URL unset and that store reports `not_configured` and is never dialled
# — which is how the test suite stays hermetic. Under ENVIRONMENT=prod all three
# are MANDATORY: the service refuses to boot without them, rather than silently
# reporting itself ready with no database.
#
# The hostnames below are Compose service names; use localhost when running the
# API outside the stack (`uv run uvicorn ...`) against `docker compose up`.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://platform:platform@postgres:5432/platform
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379/0
QDRANT_URL=http://qdrant:6333
# --- Datastore pooling (ADR 0005) ---
# DB_POOL_MIN_SIZE=1
# DB_POOL_MAX_SIZE=10
# REDIS_POOL_MAX_CONNECTIONS=10
# QDRANT_POOL_MAX_CONNECTIONS=10
# DATASTORE_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=5.0
# DATASTORE_PROBE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=2.0
# --- Anthropic / agent loop (ADR 0006) ---
# THIS IS A SECRET. Do NOT put a real key in this file or in any committed file
# — this line is a placeholder showing the variable name only. Export it in your
# shell, or inject it via Docker Compose `environment:` / CI secrets.
#
#   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# Under ENVIRONMENT=prod it is MANDATORY: the service refuses to boot without it,
# rather than starting and 401ing on every request.
#
# The `test` profile IGNORES it entirely — the suite cannot construct a real
# Anthropic client at all, so a key in your shell will never be billed by a test
# run (ADR 0009).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# ANTHROPIC_MAX_TOKENS=4096            # the API requires max_tokens on every call
# ANTHROPIC_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=60.0
# AGENT_MAX_STEPS=6                    # bounds the reason -> act loop (model calls)
# --- Voyage AI / embeddings (ADR 0011) ---
# THIS IS A SECRET. Do NOT put a real key in this file or in any committed file
# — this line is a placeholder showing the variable name only. Export it in your
# shell, or inject it via Docker Compose `environment:` / CI secrets.
#
#   export VOYAGE_API_KEY=pa-...
#
# Anthropic has no embeddings API; Voyage is the documented pairing for Claude on
# RAG workloads. This is the SECOND paid vendor the platform talks to.
#
# Under ENVIRONMENT=prod it is MANDATORY: the service refuses to boot without it,
# rather than starting and answering every question ungrounded — which looks like
# it worked, and is therefore worse than failing.
#
# The `test` profile IGNORES it entirely — the suite cannot construct a real
# Voyage client at all, so a key in your shell will never be billed by a test
# run (ADR 0011). Tests embed with a deterministic offline hash instead.
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=
# VOYAGE_MODEL=voyage-3.5-lite
# VOYAGE_EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS=1024     # MUST match the Qdrant collection's vector size
# VOYAGE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=30.0
# --- Security / auth (Stage 8, ADR 0019) ---
# THIS IS A SECRET. Do NOT put a real value in this file or in any committed
# file — these two lines are placeholders showing the variable names only.
# Export them in your shell, or inject via Docker Compose `environment:` / CI
# secrets.
#
# API_KEYS holds principal:hexhash pairs (comma-separated for multiple keys).
# API_KEY_HASH_SECRET is the server-side pepper HMAC'd into each key before
# comparison — never the raw key itself. Generate a pair with
# scripts/generate_api_key.py.
#
# Under ENVIRONMENT=prod both are MANDATORY: the service refuses to boot
# without them, rather than serving an unauthenticated API.
#
# The `test` profile does not require them — auth is exercised directly
# against RedisRateLimiter/ApiKeyAuthProvider in unit tests, not via a live key.
# API_KEYS=
# API_KEY_HASH_SECRET=
# RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=60
# RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_SECONDS=60
# --- Retrieval / Qdrant (ADR 0012, 0013) ---
# QDRANT_COLLECTION=documents
# CHUNK_SIZE_TOKENS=512                # must be > CHUNK_OVERLAP_TOKENS
# CHUNK_OVERLAP_TOKENS=64
# RETRIEVAL_TOP_K=4
# --- Conversation cache (ADR 0008) ---
# CONVERSATION_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300